## 1. Executive Summary

---

This report documents the complete compromise of 'Scrambled' Windows Active Directory machines on HackTheBox. The environment had NTLM disabled, making a specific exception for Kerberos — a non-trivial configuration that requires protocol specifics.

Attack Chain:
• Credential Discovery from Web Page Enumeration + Image Metadata
• Kerberosting of SqlSvc Account → Offline Crack → Pegasus60
• Silver Ticket Attack to Impersonate Administrator to MSSQL
• RCE via xp_cmdshell → Reverse Shell as sqlsvc
• Privilege Escalation: SeImpersonatePrivilege + JuicyPotatoNG → SYSTEM

| **RESULT** | Complete compromise — NT AUTHORITY\SYSTEM |
