## 5. Kerberoasting

---

> Kerberosting is an attack against AD accounts that have Service Principal Names (SPNs) configured. Any domain user can request a TGS ticket for any SPN — the ticket is encrypted with the hash of the service account and can be cracked offline.
> 

### 5.1Getting a TGT Ticket

| **🎯 Why** | **⚙️ How** |
| --- | --- |
| With NTLM disabled, we cannot authenticate directly with standard tools. We need a TGT (Kerberos ticket) first, which then serves as a 'passport' to request other services like GetUserSPNs. | impacket's getTGT.py retrieves the TGT from the KDC using ksimpson's credentials. It is stored in .ccache (Kerberos Credential Cache) format. The KRB5CCNAME variable tells other tools where to find the ticket. |

```bash
python3 getTGT.py scrm.local/ksimpson:ksimpson  
