### 5.2 SPN discovery and Kerberosting

| **🎯 Why** | **⚙️ How** |
| --- | --- |
| Kerberosting works because: (1) Any domain user can request a TGS ticket for any SPN. (2) The TGS is encrypted with the NTLM hash of the service account. (3) We can break it offline without alerting the system. RC4 encryption is very weak and is easily broken with hashcat. | GetUserSPNs.py requests the KDC TGS ticket for the SPNs found. The -request flag returns the ticket hash in hashcat ready format (krb5tgs).  |

