### **5.3 Hash Cracking me Hashcat**

| **🎯 Why** | **⚙️ How** |
| --- | --- |
| Offline cracking is the main advantage of Kerberosting. The attack happens on our machine, not on the DC so there is no risk of detection. | Hashcat mode 13100 is used to crack Kerberos TGS-REP tickets encrypted with RC4-HMAC (etype 23), commonly obtained during Kerberoasting attacks.

We use the rockyou.txt wordlist to attempt password cracking against the extracted hash. |

We break the hash with hashcat and discover the password

```bash
hashcat -m 13100 -a 0  hash.txt rockyou.txt

